Preheat the #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%mins}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot off the heat.

Add a knob of @?butter{} and a splash of @?milk{} or @water{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}.

Roughly chop the @mushrooms{150%grams}.

Place a large #pan{} over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When hot, add the onion and cook until softened, ~{2-3%mins}.

Add mushrooms and garlic.

Cook, stirring, until mushrooms are starting to char, ~{3-4%mins}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add @peas{120%grams}, @Worcester Sauce{1%sachet} and @passata{1%pack}.

Cook, stirring often, until the veg is coated, ~{1-2%mins}.

Add @Vegetable Stock{1%sachet}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%ml}. Bring to the boil.

> Double both sugar and water for 4p.

Once boiling, reduce heat to medium-low.

Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens slightly and veg is tender, ~{3-4%mins}.

> Add a splash of water if you feel the sauce is too thick.

Transfer the filling to an appropriately-sized #oven dish{}.

Top with the mashed potatoes. Use a #spoon{} to spread out in an even layer.

Sprinkle the @Grated Cheese{50%grams} over the top.

Bake on the middle shelf of the oven until the topping begins to brown, ~{5-6%mins}.

Remove your mushroom cottage pie from the oven.

Allow to cool for a couple of mins before serving.

Divide between plates.